’s important not to restate deterministic entries. I also need to note the risk of an optional OAuth2 dependency. The local server should bind to localhost, and we can use an in-process Vert.x HttpServer without needing Docker or an external service.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker service is needed for meaningful vertx-web-client coverage; tests can use an in-process Vert.x HTTP server. Native runs for Vert.x 5.0.1 still need the same Netty Java 25 unsafe-access runtime properties already used for 5.0.0.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For nativeTest/native-image runtime execution of io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 on JDK 25, configure runtime system properties: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. Meaningful tests should create a local Vertx instance plus local HttpServer on 127.0.0.1 and exercise WebClient requests/responses, JSON bodies, forms/multipart, redirects, cookies/session, and caching without relying on external network services.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The artifact contains OAuth2WebClient, but vertx-auth-oauth2 is an optional dependency; only add io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2:5.0.1 if the generated tests deliberately target OAuth2WebClient APIs.\",\n    \"Tests must close WebClient, HttpServer, AsyncFile, and Vertx instances to avoid async resource leaks and native-test hangs.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_008b30d1b0350827016a405d5068048196b3ca06f1f3a985ae\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 621, "output": 809, "cacheRead": 26624, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 28054, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782603076589, "responseId": "resp_008b30d1b0350827016a405d4572888196a63c2118a4f0ff11"}, "t